\begin_layout Abstract
We show that we can construct a molecular DFT by doing a second order expansion
 around an homogeneous reference fluid.
 This functional depends of the one particle solvent density and of the
 polarization.
 For computational and physical reason we restrict this expansion at the
 second order.
 We present here to possible devellopements which differs by the degree
 of desciption of the polarization field.
 In the first case we consider only the restriction at the dipolar order
 of the polarizarion whereas in the second case we consider all the multipolar
 order of the Polarization field.
\end_layout

